<h2>Work</h2>

<p>I'm currently a Senior Data Analyst at McAfee, working on product analytics, retention, and revenue optimization. Previously, I've worked in enterprise risk at a Big 5 bank and supply chain analytics at an F500 manufacturer. These days I'm also into AI/ML and experimenting with what's possible when you run models locally. Check out my <a href="https://github.com/carteakey">projects</a>.</p>

<p>Here's a visual breakdown of <a href="/skills/">where my skills lie</a> across the data landscape.</p>

<h2>Interests</h2>

<p><strong>Gaming:</strong> Massive Soulsborne fan. Bloodborne's lore lives rent-free in my head. I also dabble in retro gaming and emulation when the nostalgia hits.</p>

<p><strong>Movies:</strong> Big on horror and sci-fi. The Thing (1982) is peak cinema and I will die on that hill. I can (and will) rewatch the Dark Knight trilogy at any time.</p>

<p><strong>Tech &amp; Self-hosting:</strong> I run a home server on a repurposed laptop and self-host everything I can. I believe in the indie web, RSS feeds, and ethical ads. This blog runs on the NEAT stack (Netlify, Eleventy, Alpine.js, Tailwind) and I've let AI agents loose on it - the commit history is wild.</p>

<p><strong>Organization:</strong> I organize my life in Obsidian and call my vault "Vault 76" (yes, like Fallout). I've written about my <a href="/blog/vault-76-my-obsidian-vault-structure">vault structure</a> if you're into that sort of thing.</p>

